results.name: Prime factorization of n encoded with the run lengths of binary expansion + 1.
link: Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
example: a(9) = 7 = 1+6 (1 + 110) as 9 = 3^2 * 2^(1-1). (The run lengths of 6, 110 in binary are 2 and 1).
